Unocal Corp said its Desert Powersubsidiary began construction of a 47,500 kilowatt geothermalplant in Southern California's Imperial Valley.    The company said Desert Power expects the plant to beoperational by early 1989.    The new plant will be located at the southern end of theSalton Sea, about one-half mile from an existing 10,000kilowatt generating plant owned and operated by SouthernCalifornia Edison Co &lt;SEC>, Unocal also said. Reuter&#3;